'''Buena Vista Pumping Plant''' is a [[water pumping]] plant of the [[California State Water Project]], located 22 miles (36 km) southwest of [[Bakersfield, California|Bakersfield]], within Kern County, in the [[San Joaquin Valley]], central California. 

The plant is the third pumping plant for the [[California Aqueduct]]. From Buena Vista, water flows to the [[Edmonston Pumping Plant]], approximately 40 miles southeast, before being pumped over the [[Tehachapi Mountains]].

