{{otheruses|Family Secret (disambiguation)}}
A '''family secret''' is a [[Secrecy|secret]] kept within a [[family]]. Most families have secrets, but the kind and importance vary. Family secrets can be shared by the whole family, by some family members or kept by an individual member of the family. The secret can relate to [[taboo]] topics, rule violations or just conventional secrets. Issues like [[homosexuality]], [[adultery]], [[infidelity]], [[divorce]], [[mental illness]]; [[crime]] such as [[rape]] or [[murder]]; [[Physical abuse|physical]] or [[psychological abuse]], [[child sexual abuse]]; [[sexual violence]] such as [[marital rape]] or [[pregnancy from rape]]; [[human sexual behavior]] like [[Legitimacy (family law)|premarital pregnancy]] or [[teenage pregnancy]]; [[substance abuse]] including [[alcoholism]]. More simple secrets may be personality conflicts, [[death]], [[religion]], [[academic]] performance and physical health problems.<ref name="Fall">{{cite journal|last=Fall|first=Kevin A.|author2=Lyons, Christy|date=July 2003|title=Ethical Considerations of Family Secret Disclosure and Post-Session Safety Management|journal=[[The Family Journal]]|publisher=[[International Association of Marriage and Family Counselors]], [[SAGE Publications]]|volume=11|issue= 3|pages=281–285|issn=1066-4807|url=http://tfj.sagepub.com/cgi/content/abstract/11/3/281|accessdate=2008-10-30|doi=10.1177/1066480703252339}}</ref> Any topic that a family member thinks may cause anxiety may become a family secret. Family members often see keeping the secrets as important to keeping the family working, but over time the secrets can increase the anxiety in the family.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Knauth|first=Donna G.|date=August 2003|title=Family Secrets: An Illustrative Clinical Case Study Guided by Bowen Family Systems Theory|journal=[[Journal of Family Nursing]]|publisher=[[SAGE Publications]]|volume=9|issue= 3|pages=331–344|issn=1074-8407|url=http://jfn.sagepub.com/cgi/content/abstract/9/3/331|accessdate=2008-10-30|doi=10.1177/1074840703255451}}</ref> The [[confidentiality]] of family secrets revealed by a patient is a common [[ethical dilemma]] for counselors and therapists.<ref name="Fall" />

