{{Infobox person | name = Kurt Albert | image = Kurt Albert 02.jpg | alt = | caption = Kurt Albert 1985 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1954|01|28}} | birth_place = [[Nuremberg]], [[Germany]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|2010|09|28|1954|01|28}} | death_place = [[Erlangen]], [[Bavaria]], [[Germany]] | nationality = German | other_names = | known_for = Rock climbing | occupation = Climber and Photographer }}
'''Kurt Albert''' (January 28, 1954 – September 28, 2010) was a [[climbing|climber]] and [[photographer]]. He started climbing at the age of 14. Before he wholly committed his life to climbing in 1986 he was a mathematics and physics teacher.
At the age of seventeen he climbed the Walkerpfeiler in the [[Grandes Jorasses]] and one year later he climbed the [[Eiger north face#Nordwand|north face of the Eiger]]. After a visit to the [[Saxon Switzerland]] climbing area in Saxony, Germany in 1973 he recognized the potential of [[free climbing]] (free climbing was practised in [[Saxony]] since the early 19th century). He started to free climb in his home climbing area, the [[Frankenjura]]. In the routes he would now try to ascend while free climbing, he would&mdash;in between attempts&mdash;paint a red 'X' on the rocks near pitons he did not need as holds or steps. Once he could place a red 'X' on all the pitons and hooks in the route, and was thus able to [[Free climbing|free climb]] the entire route, he would paint a red dot at the base of the route. From this comes the English term "[[Redpoint (climbing)|redpoint]]", which is derived from the German ''Rotpunkt'', meaning "red dot" or "red point". In many ways this was the origin of the free climbing movement that led to the development of [[sport climbing]] some years later.
Albert was severely injured in a climbing accident on September 26, 2010. Albert fell {{convert|18|m|ft}} while taking pictures at [[via ferrata]] ''Höhenglücksteig'' close to [[Hirschbach, Bavaria]]. Albert died two days later while hospitalised in [[Erlangen]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://alpin.de/news/news/47589d7c-c5ef-4ece-b48d-f81e5d6b82fd | title = Rätselraten um Kurt Albert | accessdate = 2010-11-01}}</ref>
== Books == * {{cite book |isbn=3-930650-15-0 |title=Kurt Albert |author=Kn Tr Benoit (Herausgeber)}} * {{cite book |first1=Kurt |last1=Albert |title=Fight gravity. Klettern im Frankenjura |year=2005 |publisher=tmms-verlag | isbn = 3-930650-16-9}}
