{{Infobox body of water | name = Liverpool Offtake Reservoir | image = | alt = | caption = | image_bathymetry = | alt_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Cecil Hills, New South Wales|Cecil Hills]], [[Sydney]], [[Australia]] | coords = {{coord|-33.889869|150.826790|type:waterbody}} | type = [[Reservoir]] | inflow = pipe from Upper Canal | outflow = Hinchinbrook Creek | catchment = | basin_countries = | agency = [[Sydney Catchment Authority]] | date-built = 1890 | length = | width = | area = | depth = | max-depth = 1933 raised {{convert|10|ft|abbr=on}} | volume = after 1933 {{convert|37|e6impgal|ML acre.ft|abbr=on}} | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | cities = [[Liverpool, New South Wales|Liverpool]] | reference = }} '''Liverpool Offtake Reservoir''' (Liverpool Dam) is a small reservoir in [[Cecil Hills]], New South Wales.<ref>{{cite web|title=Liverpool Offtake Reservoir|url=http://www.environment.nsw.gov.au/heritageapp/ViewHeritageItemDetails.aspx?ID=1970060|website=[[Office of Environment and Heritage (New South Wales)|Office of Environment & Heritage]]|publisher=[[NSW Government]]|accessdate=3 December 2016}}</ref> Built along with the [[Upper Nepean Scheme]] it replaced the [[Liverpool Weir]] supply.<!-- User:Dave Rave/Liverpool Dam -->
Built in an old council quarry it was originally used to supply water to [[Liverpool, New South Wales|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article13768242 |title=WATER SUPPLY FOR LIVERPOOL. |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |issue=16,252 |location=New South Wales, Australia |date=26 April 1890 |accessdate=4 December 2016 |page=12 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref> Various offtakes were constructed along the [[Upper Nepean Scheme|Sydney Water Supply Upper Canal]] for local district supply. It was also used to drain water from the nearby Upper Canal during maintenance.<ref>{{cite web|title=Liverpool (Mount Misery) Reservoir (WS 0061)|url=https://www.sydneywater.com.au/SW/water-the-environment/what-we-re-doing/Heritage-search/heritage-detail/index.htm?heritageid=4575814|website=[[Sydney Water]]|accessdate=3 December 2016|language=en}}</ref><ref>[http://www.sydneywater.com.au/web/groups/publicwebcontent/documents/document/zgrf/mdq0/~edisp/dd_044331.pdf Sydney Engineers] - nomination for Cataract Dam appendix 5</ref>
In 1901 another reservoir at Mount Misery, Heckenberg was constructed between this dam and Liverpool.
In 1933 the dam was cleaned out and the wall upgraded to increase its volume from {{convert|4|to|37|e6impgal|ML|abbr=out}}.
