The '''Roman Catholic Hospital''' is a private{{fact|date=June 2014}} [[hospital]] in [[Windhoek]], [[Namibia]] run by the [[Roman Catholic Church in Namibia|Roman Catholic Church]]. Founded in 1907 by the [[Order of Saint Benedict|Benedictine]] Missionary Sisters of [[Tutzing]], the Roman Catholic Hospital had 87 beds in 2007.<ref>[http://www.rcchurch.na/windhoek/health/wdh-hospital.htm Roman Catholic Hospital] Roman Catholic Church of Namibia</ref> <ref name=roman>{{cite web|title=High-quality nursing and care|url=http://www2.drapilux.com/en/marke_menschen/hospital-windhoek.php?PHPSESSID=go3lma2eo4u7lh4qisiibhfp70|publisher=drapilux.com|accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref> <ref name=africa>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Jana-Mari|title=Namibia: RC Hospital Makes History|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201104070288.html|publisher=allafrica.com|accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref>

