On June 18, 2010, The [[United States Department of Health and Human Services]] released [http://www.federalregister.gov/OFRUpload/OFRData/2010-14999_PI.pdf 45 CFR part 170], '''Establishment of the Temporary Certification Program for Health [[Information Technology]]'''

The rule establishes a temporary [[certification program]] for the purposes of testing and certifying [[health information technology]]. The
temporary certification program will authorize organizations to test and certify Complete Electronic [[Health record|Health Record]]s (EHRs) and/or EHR Modules.<ref>{{cite web|title=Temporary Certification Program|url=http://www.healthit.gov/policy-researchers-implementers/temporary-certification-program|accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref>

